runs.comm: run down to third man
flicked to long leg for his first Twenty20 run ... he made a duck in his only other match
Joyce takes three paces, Bracken tries to bowl wide to thwart him and ends up overdoing it
squirted into the covers
Joyce takes a pace down the track, looks to loft it over long-on but it goes high to Hussey who makes 20 yards to his left from mid-on to hold the steepler
jagged in to Vaughan and he works it out on the leg side
Flintoff back and blocks into the covers
decent start, whipped to deep square leg
dug in, Flintoff top edges the hook and White holds a simple catch at square leg. A dream, start for Harwood and another nightmare on the way for England so it seems
played out to cover
short, and Vaughan swivels and pulls for four, lovely shot. It's as if he's never been away
shortish outside off stump, Vaughan aims a savage swat through the covers and misses
hits the pads going down the leg side, bounces into the covers
slanted across Vaughan who can't reach it. Somehow that's not a wide, which is daft, and Vaughan laughes
pushed to the right of cover and a straightforward single
opens the face and drives to the sweeper
aims for the yorker with a slower ball, a bit fuller and Vaughan plays it straight to extra cover
again Vaughan cracks it right to extra cover
wider and Vaughan frees his arms and drives superbly to the cover boundary
short, Piertersen on it quickly and hooks the ball off his nose behind square for four
fuller, Pietersen hammers it over mid-off and gives the bowler some advice for good measure
checked drive, the ball lobs safely over Harwood
into the leg side, a quick single to test Vaughan' s knee
pitched up, driven had to mid-on where Hussey, who sprints in, fumbles and allows the second
glorious placement, flicked past the man on the 45 behind square on the leg

turned behind square on the off, Pietersen calls for a second and Harwood scores a direct hit to leave him a foot short ... had he not hit then Pietersen would have made it. The Australians think they have their man straight away - plenty of high tens - and the third umpire confirms their optimism
edged through second slip (not that such a thing exists in Twenty20) and off the mark with a four
bell opens the face and tries to place it into a gap on the off side but fails
flicked off middle and leg to Symonds at deep square leg
slower ball which deceives Vaughan as he looks to run the ball fine on the off
wide, Vaughan slashes it inches beyond the diving Clarke at cover and there's no man out on the rope
fullish awayswinger squirted into the off side
chipped back over the bowler
Vaughan forced back and he can only block it
slower ball, hit high and straight to Clarke at mid-off ... but it's a no-ball and a free hit ... and Clarke looks utterly cheesed off as well he might
Bell steps to leg, gets a thick inside edge and it shoots past Gilchrist for four. He couldn't have been out to that
worked out to the cover boundary
hit square on the off and Vaughan calls for and gets the second
short, Bell goes back and runs the ball to long-on
Vaughan aims a reverse sweep and misses, "that's out" yells the entire commentary team and the umpire agrees. Vaughan looks miffed and seems to suggest he got an edge
Collingwood waits and punches the ball to long-on
turned round the corner and Collingwood rushes through for the single
again stroked to long-on. "We'll get 'em in singles," might not be the best approach here ...
hit firmly to extra cover
short of a length, Collingwood fences and misses
tip and run to point
driven to long-off
Collingwood gets a thick edge into his pads, Hilfenhaus appeals although not sure what for
banged in, really short and it flies over Collingwood's head as he jerks out of the way
pushed into the covers
Collingwood is beaten all ends up
worked into the off side
turned to square leg
worked to leg again, ones and twos at will when more is needed
pushed into the off side
swept to long leg
turned round the corner again, well picked up
short, pulled to long-on, middled but still only the one
kept slightly low and under Collingwood's attempted flick into the off
launched high into the leg side where White waits patiently a yard inside the rope at deep midwicket and pouches the ball with nonchalant ease
punched back to the bowler
turned through midwicket to White in the deep
turned neatly round the corner
strides down the track, tries to wallop that behind square with a sweep, misses, and it clatters into him
comes down and drives that sweetly to mid-on
worked off the legs square
tries to reverse sweep that and misses out on a full toss
waits, and works that off the legs square
sashays down the track and drives that to mid-on
worked off the back foot to the man on the third-man boundary
huge call for one which is short and Nixon appears to edge that off a swipe to Gilchrist. The umpire is unmoved. Hilfy just laughs
quick single this time
straight and a full toss cleans up Bell's stumps, clattering into off stick
big away swing for that one, under the lights, bananaing away from the righthander who attempts to drive
pushed up there and Dalrymple can only defend - another dot
edge pops up off a reverse sweep and that's a sitter. What an absolutely poor drop: it doesn't stick for Stickers at fine leg
quick single this time
full and up there and there's a big call, with Gilchrist trying to reverse tickle that onto the stumps in follow up - he misses, but the batsman would have been back in his crease
defended this time
a reverse sweep pops into space off the back of the bat
sweep and the ball... reaches the boundary! Crack open the beers
wide down the leg-side and that's chased ineffectually
shot, down the ground with an extra-cover drive off the back foot
shelled - and that's Haydos at a straightish midwicket - pops in and out but he can laugh; Australia can afford to, frankly
over the wicket at the left hander and that's swiped back at him
down the ground with an aerial drive and that's one bounce to long-on
walks across his stumps and sweeps that off his toes down to fine leg. Harwood spits out his disgust
sweep, missed and that crashes into the pad
on one knee, swept off his front foot behind square and that nutmegs Harwood who's then forced to give chase
goes aerial with a cover-drive and that thuds into the ground inside the boundary
down the ground, straight drive, and that brings up four runs - full face of the bat, a better shot
a reverse sweep again, doesn't get much power on it, and that goes right to the Bear
plays that off the front foot behind point and there's a quickly run two
pushed up there and dug out to gully
wide and the batsman shapes to sweep but is too late on the shot
the batsman nearly yorks himself there, moving over to that one which pitches on leg and he digs it out
defence this time
low full toss pulled into the leg-side without much power
quick single
reverse sweep
drops that a touch wide, on leg, and that's worked into the leg-side
Gilchrist missed an easy stumping, popping up off his gloves - a legspinner which didn't spin

missed an easy stumping, popping up off his gloves - a legspinner which didn't spin

the batsman misses that one
short and helped over the top off the full face of the bat, lovely shot through cover
reverse sweep, over the top, and he gets away with that
single off the back foot into the covers
quicker one at 65mpph (106kmh), low full toss and the batsman rushes at that one, and misses
drives into his feet
slower ball
slower one, on leg, and there's a chance for a run-out at the stumps, which misses, and there's an overthrow
goes for the reverse sweep
very, very plumb. Reverse sweep, and that one keeps low. Dalrymple isn't amused, but he's out - plum duff, really
leg-side wide this time
driven to a straight long-off position
short, and that's whipped off the back foot to cover
stifled this time
comes down the wicket, and Lewis takes a big whoosh at that one, gets a fine edge and Gilchrist takes it cleanly, whipping the bails off for good measure
on the leg-side and that's swept behind square - huge cheers
wide and Nixon tries to cut that off the back foot, too late on the shot
clipped on the leg-side but with not enough power to reach Symonds, the man in the deep
swung away into the leg-side and that's the first six of the innings
short and wide full bunger, driven to mid-off
Bouncer, Panesar misses out and tries to get the bye after Nixon's call for the strike, but he's run out easily at the non-striker's end
a one-bounce four, lovely shot for what it's worth - aerial straight drive
pitched up there, dug out, and driven to mid-off
eased away down to third man and that's the end - Australia bossing that match
